Bob, the Consulting Partner explained, "The first industrial revolution was mechanization led by water and steam. This gave us steam engines and trains. The second industrial revolution was mass production, led by electric power. This gave us mass production and huge machinery driven by electricity. The third industrial revolution was automation, led by electronics and IT. This gave us the Personal Computer, the Internet, the mobile phone and many more. The fourth, loosely speaking, is the Age of Artificial Intelligence and associated technologies that drive business transformation".